headline: Erie Indemnity (ERIE) Misses Q2 Earnings and Revenue Estimates
summary: Erie Indemnity (ERIE) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of -5.92% and -2.55%, respectively, for the quarter ended June 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: Erie Indemnity: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: ERIE, Pa. AP) — Erie Indemnity Co. (ERIE) on Thursday reported profit of $174.7 million in its second quarter. The Erie, Pennsylvania-based company said it had profit of $3.34 per share.

headline: Erie Indemnity Reports Second Quarter 2025 Results
summary: Erie Indemnity Company (NASDAQ: ERIE) today announced financial results for the quarter and six months ending June 30, 2025. Net income was $174.7 million, or $3.34 per diluted share, in the second quarter of 2025, compared to $163.9 million, or $3.13 per diluted share, in the second quarter of 2024. Net income was $313.1 million, or $5.99 per diluted share, in the first six months of 2025, compared to $288.5 million, or $5.52 per diluted share, in the first six months of 2024.
